# Key Formula

For two adjacent restrictions

```text
(id1, h1) -------- (id2, h2)
```

with

```text
distance = id2 - id1
```

the highest achievable peak between them is

```python
peak = (h1 + h2 + distance) // 2
```

because we can increase by 1 from the left side and decrease by 1 from the right side until both slopes meet.

